Imade Adeleke, the first daughter of Afrobeats star Davido, has tackle her father over his attitude towards fans. The father and daughter were seen cruising in the singer’s Lamborghini Aventador he bought for himself last Christmas. As the DMW boss drove with his daughter right next to him on the passenger side, the 6-year-old asked why he wasn’t acknowledging fans’ greetings.   Rick Ross replaces Burna Boy at Afro Nation     Oyibo Rebel: Naija babes have a place in my heart     Burna Boy, Rema, Buju, top Nigeria’s Spotify chart   “Daddy why aren’t you saying, ‘hi!?” Imade asked. Davido responded: ‘I am’ with a smile on his face. The young Imade however, made sure to cover up for her super star dad as she could be seen smiling and displaying the ‘thumbs up’ sign to the hailing fans.